PROJECT: Old Money – Interest-on-Interest Calculator
FORMAT: Minimalistic Functional Specification

---------------------------------------------------------
1. INPUT FIELDS
---------------------------------------------------------
- Input A: "Saving Start Amount"
  - Type: numeric text field
  - Validation: positive number
  - Calculation trigger: ON BLUR (when field loses focus)

- Input B: "Yearly Average Interest (%)"
  - Type: numeric text field
  - Validation: positive number, decimals allowed
  - Calculation trigger: ON BLUR (when field loses focus)

- Calculation triggers automatically when input blurs.
- No real-time keystroke calculation (improves performance).

---------------------------------------------------------
2. CALCULATION LOGIC
---------------------------------------------------------
- Year 0 = Start Amount
- Year N = Year(N-1) * (1 + interest/100)
- Interest compounded yearly.
- Values rounded to 2 decimals.
- Monthly Equivalent = End-of-Year Amount / 12
- Yearly Increase = End-of-Year(N) – End-of-Year(N-1)

---------------------------------------------------------
3. OUTPUT TABLE GROUPS (COLLAPSIBLE/TOGGLABLE)
---------------------------------------------------------
Group 1: Years 1–10
Group 2: Years 11–30
Group 3: Years 31–40

Each group is COLLAPSIBLE:
- Desktop: Groups open by default (all visible on load)
- Tablet (iPad Pro): Groups collapsed by default (user expands as needed)
- Mobile (iPhone 17 Max + others): Groups collapsed by default

Collapsible means: Click group header to expand/collapse content
Purpose: Better performance on mobile, less scrolling
Toggle behavior: Smooth collapse/expand animation (0.3s)

Each table row contains:
- Year Index (1, 2, 3…)
- Start-of-Yea & ALIGNMENT
-------------------------------------------------
General Alignment Rules:
- DEFAULT: Always align LEFT when nothing else is specified
- Text labels: LEFT-aligned
- Headers: LEFT-aligned
- Year index: LEFT-aligned
- Numeric values: RIGHT-aligned (for easy reading)

Row Spacing:
- Row height: 28-32px (mobile), 32-36px (desktop/tablet)
- Cell padding: 8px horizontal, 6px vertical
- Row borders: Thin, 1px solid #C8C8C8

Header row: Sticky (fixed when scrolling)
Groups: Visually separated with thin borders
Numeric values: Right-aligned for alignment
Year index: Left-aligned-----------
4. TABLE RULES
---------------------------------------------------------
- Tight row spacing, minimal padding.
- Numeric values right-aligned.
- Year index left-aligned.
- Header row fixed when scrolling.
- Groups visually separated with thin borders.

---------------------------------------------------------
5. SUMMARY SECTION - BEST PRACTICES FOR ALL TERMINALS
-----------------------------------------

DESKTOP (standard widths 1024px+):
- Tables full width
- Groups OPEN by default (all visible)
- Two-column layout possible
- Full feature visibility
- No truncation

TABLET / iPAD PRO (768px - 1024px):
- Tables full width, responsive padding
- Groups COLLAPSED by default (user expands)
- Single-column layout
- Touch-friendly button sizing (48px minimum)
- Maintain readability

MOBILE / iPHONE 17 MAX & OTHERS (< 768px):
- Tables scroll horizontally (if needed)
- Groups COLLAPSED by default (user expands)
- Single-column layout
- Vertical stacking for columns
- Monthly + Yearly columns may stack vertically OR use abbreviations
- Font sizes reduced but readable (14px minimum)
- Full-width inputs and buttons
- Vertical margin increased for tap targets (44px minimum)
- Tables full width.
- Groups open by default.


7. ERROR HANDLING
---------------------------------------------------------
- Empty inputs: disable calculation.
- Invalid inputs: minimal inline warning.
- Interest = 0: show table with no growth.

---------------------------------------------------------
8. EXPORT OPTIONS
---------------------------------------------------------
- Export to CSV.
- Copy-to-clipboard (plain numbers, no currency formatting).

---------------------------------------------------------
9. NUMBER FORMATTING
---------------------------------------------------------
- Plain numbers only.
- No currency symbols.
- No thousand separators.

---------------------------------------------------------
10. IMPROVEMENTS ADDED
---------------------------------------------------------
- Automatic recalculation on input change.
- Percentage growth added to summary.
- Export options included.
- Monthly equivalent clarified.
- Long-term grouping extended to 40 years.

---------------------------------------------------------
END OF FUNCTIONAL SPECIFICATION
---------------------------------------------------------
